      {
        "id": 3886050,
        "name": "Tom Won",
        "username": "Tom_Won",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/85e7bf/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2022-09-04T00:03:44.716Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-Monopole_Cru\" data-username=\"B.Kelly\" data-post=\"6\" data-topic=\"287665\" data-full=\"true\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/b.kelly/48/3888_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> B.Kelly:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Can you elaborate on the cheese note?  Is it a funky blue cheese note, parmesan, something else?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>It can get pretty funky but definitely not blue cheese level funky. I\u2019d say it felt more like aged cheddar. Quite unique profile paired with its acidity. I don\u2019t usually drink bdb that often but when I do, this and the C+C are my top picks.</p>",
